io.sarl.sre.services.probing

Class FieldProbe<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.sarl.sre.services.probing.AbstractProbe<T>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Probe<T>

    public class FieldProbe<T>
extends AbstractFieldProbe<T>
    Probe implementation is linked to a field. A probe is thread-safe. This probe buferrizes the values. In order to be updated, the Probe.sync() function must be invoked. Then, the new value is read from the associated field, and the probe listeners are notified.
